args: Oh, er, I'm sorry as well...
(I made up my mind to travel the world\noutside of the hidden village, but I still\ncan't quite get used to all this.)
(I'm always on edge, watching over my\nshoulder. It wasn't like this when I was\nwith him...)
(I miss Tobias. But where would I even go\nto see him again?)
(I think I'm nearly there, but I still don't\nsee anything resembling a castle.)
(Did I take a wrong turn? Maybe I should\nstop and ask someone.)
Huh. That crowd is awfully noisy.
Done already? As I recall, YOU\nwere the one to challenge ME.
I'll pay every coin back, I swear!\nSo please, I beg you! Spare me!
You will do as you've promised, and\nfurthermore, you will never return to\nthis village. Swear it.
I do, merciful lady! I swear!\n...Goodbye!
Thank you, dearie.\nYou've been a huge help.
Think nothing of it. I could scarcely allow\na merchant in name only to continue\nperpetrating his fraud here.
Ha ha. Thank you. If you have any troubles\nin the future, do let me know.
I shall come running from the Halidom.
Hm? Yours is a face I haven't seen around\nthese parts.
I'm Nino. I'm trying to get to the Halidom\nto see a man called Tobias.

Ah, you're a friend of Tobias! I'm Elisanne.
I trained together with Tobias at the
Church, and these days I reside at the
Halidom.
I'm afraid he's not at the castle now,\nthough.
He's not? Argh. What should I do, then?
You would be welcome to stay at the\ncastle until he returns, if you like.
You'll have no worry of accidentally\nmissing one another that way. I doubt\nhe'll be long.
Not at all. Shall we, then?
(But she's so much more mature. She's\npoised and regal and well-respected.)
(The outside world has so many kinds of\npeople...)
You all right, Nino? This is your welcome\nparty! Eat up!
Is the food not to your taste?
Oh, no, it's delicious. I've just never eaten\nin such a...lively setting before.
This is pretty much normal around here!\nNot much of a party animal, girlio?
Maybe not? But it's nice to watch\nothers having a good time.
As long as we're not freakin' you out. So,\nwhat was it like back home for you, Nino?
Yeah, don't let us hog the conversation all\nnight, or we'll never learn anything about\nyou!
Go on, tell us everything! Dish!
(If I told them I was Ilia's descendant,\nthey would never treat me like this again.)
(And that's the last thing I want.)
I lived alone, out in the woods. But I've\nbeen traveling, ever since I met Tobias.
(Better that I keep my secrets close.)
(I've only just forged these new\nconnections...and I'd hate to see\nthem ruined so soon.)
